401.definition: [ἀνάχυσις] from a comparative of {{G303}} and χέω (to pour); properly, effusion, i.e. (figuratively) license

403.definition: [ἀνάψυξις] from {{G404}}; properly, a recovery of breath, i.e. (figuratively) revival

404.definition: [ἀναψύχω] from {{G303}} and {{G5594}}; properly, to cool off, i.e. (figuratively) relieve

405.definition: [ἀνδραποδιστής] from a derivative of a compound of {{G435}} and {{G4228}}; an enslaver (as bringing men to his feet)

407.definition: [ἀνδρίζομαι] middle voice from {{G435}}; to act manly

408.definition: [Ἀνδρόνικος] from {{G435}} and {{G3534}}; man of victory; Andronicos, an Israelite

410.definition: [ἀνέγκλητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G1458}}; unaccused, i.e. (by implication) irreproachable

411.definition: [ἀνεκδιήγητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G1555}}; not expounded in full, i.e. indescribable

412.definition: [ἀνεκλάλητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G1583}}; not spoken out, i.e. (by implication) unutterable

413.definition: [ἀνέκλειπτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G1587}}; not left out, i.e. (by implication) inexhaustible

414.definition: [ἀνεκτότερος] comparative of a derivative of {{G430}}; more endurable

415.definition: [ἀνελεήμων] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G1655}}; merciless

416.definition: [ἀνεμίζω] from {{G417}}; to toss with the wind

417.definition: [ἄνεμος] from the base of {{G109}}; wind; (plural) by implication, (the four) quarters (of the earth)

418.definition: [ἀνένδεκτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as {{G1735}}; unadmitted, i.e. (by implication) not supposable

419.definition: [ἀνεξερεύνητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G1830}}; not searched out, i.e. (by implication) inscrutable

420.definition: [ἀνεξίκακος] from {{G430}} and {{G2556}}; enduring of ill, i.e. forbearing

421.definition: [ἀνεξιχνίαστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{G1537}} and a derivative of {{G2487}}; not tracked out, i.e. (by implication) untraceable

422.definition: [ἀνεπαίσχυντος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G153}}; not ashamed, i.e. irreprehensible:

423.definition: [ἀνεπίληπτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G1949}}; not arrested, i.e. (by implication) inculpable

426.definition: [ἀνετάζω] from {{G303}} and ἐτάζω (to test); to investigate (judicially)

428.definition: [ἀνεύθετος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G2111}}; not well set, i.e. inconvenient

430.definition: [ἀνέχομαι] middle voice from {{G303}} and {{G2192}}; to hold oneself up against, i.e. (figuratively) put up with

431.definition: [ἀνεψιός] from {{G1}} (as a particle of union) and an obsolete νέπος (a brood); properly, akin, i.e. (specially) a cousin

433.definition: [ἀνήκω] from {{G303}} and {{G2240}}; to attain to, i.e. (figuratively) be proper

434.definition: [ἀνήμερος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and ἥμερος (lame); savage

435.definition: [ἀνήρ] a primary word (compare {{G444}}); a man (properly as an individual male)

436.definition: [ἀνθίστημι] from {{G473}} and {{G2476}}; to stand against, i.e. oppose

437.definition: [ἀνθομολογέομαι] from {{G473}} and the middle voice of {{G3670}}; to confess in turn, i.e. respond in praise

439.definition: [ἀνθρακιά] from {{G440}}; a bed of burning coals

440.definition: [ἄνθραξ] of uncertain derivation; a live coal

443.definition: [ἀνθρωποκτόνος] from {{G444}} and κτείνω(to kill); a manslayer Compare {{G5406}}.

444.definition: [ἄνθρωπος] from {{G435}} and ὤψ (the countenance; from {{G3700}}); man-faced, i.e. a human being

446.definition: [ἀνθύπατος] from {{G473}} and a superlative of {{G5228}}; instead of the highest officer, i.e. (specially) a Roman proconsul

447.definition: [ἀνίημι] from {{G303}} and ἵημι (to send); to let up, i.e. (literally) slacken or (figuratively) desert, desist from

448.definition: [ἀνίλεως] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G2436}}; inexorable

449.definition: [ἄνιπτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G3538}}; without ablution

450.definition: [ἀνίστημι] from {{G303}} and {{G2476}}; to stand up (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive)

451.definition: [Ἄννα] of Hebrew origin ({{H2584}}); Anna, an Israelitess

452.definition: [Ἄννας] of Hebrew origin ({{H2608}}); Annas (i.e. {{G367}}), an Israelite

453.definition: [ἀνόητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G3539}}; unintelligent; by implication, sensual

454.definition: [ἄνοια] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3563}}; stupidity; by implication, rage

455.definition: [ἀνοίγω] from {{G303}} and οἴγω (to open); to open up (literally or figuratively, in various applications)

458.definition: [ἀνομία] from {{G459}}; illegality, i.e. violation of law or (genitive case) wickedness

459.definition: [ἄνομος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3551}}; lawless, i.e. (negatively) not subject to (the Jewish) law; (by implication, a Gentile), or (positively) wicked

460.definition: [ἀνόμως] adverb from {{G459}}; lawlessly, i.e. (specially) not amenable to (the Jewish) law

461.definition: [ἀνορθόω] from {{G303}} and a derivative of the base of {{G3717}}; to straighten up

462.definition: [ἀνόσιος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3741}}; wicked

465.definition: [ἀντάλλαγμα] from a compound of {{G473}} and {{G236}}; an equivalent or ransom

467.definition: [ἀνταποδίδωμι] from {{G473}} and {{G591}}; to requite (good or evil)

470.definition: [ἀνταποκρίνομαι] from {{G473}} and {{G611}}; to contradict or dispute

471.definition: [ἀντέπω] from {{G473}} and {{G2036}}; to refute or deny

472.definition: [ἀντέχομαι] from {{G473}} and the middle voice of {{G2192}}; to hold oneself opposite to, i.e. (by implication) adhere to; by extension to care for

473.definition: [ἀντί] a primary particle; opposite, i.e. instead or because of (rarely in addition to) Often used in composition to denote contrast, requital, substitution, correspondence, etc.

475.definition: [ἀντιδιατίθεμαι] from {{G473}} and {{G1303}}; to set oneself opposite, i.e. be  disputatious

476.definition: [ἀντίδικος] from {{G473}} and {{G1349}}; an opponent (in a lawsuit); specially, Satan (as the arch-enemy)

477.definition: [ἀντίθεσις] from a compound of {{G473}} and {{G5087}}; opposition, i.e. a conflict (of theories)

478.definition: [ἀντικαθίστημι] from {{G473}} and {{G2525}}; to set down (troops) against, i.e. withstand

479.definition: [ἀντικαλέω] from {{G473}} and {{G2564}}; to invite in return

480.definition: [ἀντίκειμαι] from {{G473}} and {{G2749}}; to lie opposite, i.e. be adverse (figuratively, repugnant) to

482.definition: [ἀντιλαμβάνομαι] from {{G473}} and the middle voice of {{G2983}}; to take hold of in turn, i.e. succor; also to participate

485.definition: [ἀντιλογία] from a derivative of {{G483}}; dispute, disobedience

486.definition: [ἀντιλοιδορέω] from {{G473}} and {{G3058}}; to rail in reply

488.definition: [ἀντιμετρέω] from {{G473}} and {{G3354}}; to mete in return

489.definition: [ἀντιμισθία] from a compound of {{G473}} and {{G3408}}; requital, correspondence

490.definition: [Ἀντιόχεια] from Ἀντίοχυς (a Syrian king); Antiochia, a place in Syria

491.definition: [Ἀντιοχεύς] from {{G490}}; an Antiochian or inhabitant of Antiochia

492.definition: [ἀντιπαρέρχομαι] from {{G473}} and {{G3928}}; to go along opposite

493.definition: [Ἀντίπας] contracted for a compound of {{G473}} and a derivative of {{G3962}}; Antipas, a Christian

494.definition: [Ἀντιπατρίς] from the same as {{G493}}; Antipatris, a place in Palestine

495.definition: [ἀντιπέραν] from {{G473}} and {{G4008}}; on the opposite side

496.definition: [ἀντιπίπτω] from {{G473}} and {{G4098}} (including its alternate); to oppose

497.definition: [ἀντιστρατεύομαι] from {{G473}} and {{G4754}}; (figuratively) to attack, i.e. (by implication) destroy

498.definition: [ἀντιτάσσομαι] from {{G473}} and the middle voice of {{G5021}}; to range oneself against, i.e. oppose

499.definition: [ἀντίτυπον] neuter of a compound of {{G473}} and {{G5179}}; corresponding ("antitype"), i.e. a representative, counterpart

500.definition: [ἀντίχριστος] from {{G473}} and {{G5547}}; an opponent of the Messiah
